author: Brent Axe | baxe@syracuse.com
title: Syracuse Basketball: See where Orange and opponents rank in poll of all 351 teams
text:
With the 2015-16 Syracuse basketball season just around the corner, the preseason rankings are flowing like apple cider.
You can find Syracuse projected to finish somewhere between fifth and ninth in the ACC , according to some leading preseason magazines and websites.
CBS Sports took the preseason rankings game to a whole new level and decided to rank all 351 teams in Division I college basketball.
The CBS college hoops staff put Syracuse at No. 43 on the list .
One of those SU rosters that Orange fans are feeling ambivalent about. Perhaps a bubble team. We're not seeing top-25 caliber here, but certainly a step up from last season. There will be plenty of time to see if that ranking is too high or too low (I think it's a bit low to be honest).
Playing in the ACC will certainly bring some tough opponents to Syracuse's schedule, including North Carolina, who ranks No.1 in the CBS poll.
But how does Syracuse's full 2015-16 schedule coincide with CBS' ranking?
Below are the teams on the Syracuse basketball schedule as they appear in the CBS ranking.
